The paper deals with decoding algorithms for linear codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.ITP). The use of matrix-product codes suggests a connection to algebraic coding theory (cs.DS) and combinatorial designs (cs.DM). The mention of error-correction capability also suggests a connection to error-correcting codes (cs.CC).
